<TITLE> Speaker meets BNP over return </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 19 (bdnews24.com)The main opposition BNP Thursday had a closed-door meeting with speaker Abdul Hamid over its return to the parliament. MPs of the party and its allies have been skipping proceedings since Jan. 28, the second working day of the ninth parliament. Chief whip Abdus Shahid and chief whip of the opposition Zainul Abdin Farroque met with Hamid after the he invited both of them to settle the row over the seat arrangements. "The final decision about joining the parliament will come at the Sunday's meeting in presence of the leader of the opposition in the parliament," Faorroque told reporters after the meeting with Shahid. "I have had a meeting with them (BNP) and urged them to rejoin the session," speaker Hamid told bdnews24.com at his office. He said he renewed his call to the opposition lawmakers to return to the parliament. "I will try to resolve the matter in a honourable way in the next session," he said. On Jan. 28, the newly-elected speaker reshuffled the seating arrangements for the MPs, pushing five out of nine of BNP MPs members to the back bench. The immediate-past speaker Jamiruddin Sircar had allocated nine seats on the front row for the BNP, which won 29 seats in 300-strong parliament. But the treasury bench said the opposition will get only there seats on the front row according to their strength, although the former speaker had given them nine. Asked about Thursday's decision of the meeting, Shahid said his position remained unchanged. "No question of making concessions for them comes," he told bdnews24.com. bd
